{
  "texts": [
    "Reusable materials include not only source code but also more abstract elements such as designs and overviews.",
    "This approach can enhance the efficiency of development by leveraging existing knowledge.",
    "However, a challenge associated with software upcycling is the difficulty in conceiving ideas for how to upcycle effectively.Our prior research developed the SUCCEED system [9].",
    "An upcycling case includes software materials (e.g., source code and design documents) that were useful in some past development, along with background information leading to that development and post-product evaluation as supplementary information.",
    "Each case comprises four elements: context, representing the development background; materials, representing the materials used in development; recipe, indicating the specific development methodology; and result, reflecting the evaluation of the development."
  ]
}